Class SetOfPredicatesWithTerms

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,SetOfStrings>
        • es.csic.iiia.nsm.agent.language.SetOfPredicatesWithTerms
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,SetOfStrings>

    public class SetOfPredicatesWithTerms
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,SetOfStrings>
    A set of predicates with terms. It consists in a set of predicates, where each predicate contains a non-empty set of terms. The set of predicates has the form p_1(t_1, ..., t_n), ..., p_m(t_1, ..., t_m), where p_i stands for the ith predicate and t_j stands for the jth term of a predicate
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"
